title: Young woman dies ‘after crashing jet ski into boyfriend’ on LAST DAY of dream holiday
text:
FACEBOOK TRAGIC: Emily Jayne Collie was killed after crashing her jet ski into boyfriend Tommy Keating 
Emily Jayne Collie, 20, died after a jet ski she was riding collided with one ridden by her boyfriend Tommy Keating on the party island of Phuket on Sunday. 
Tourists and lifeguards on Kata Beach desperately battled to save the pretty blonde – but she died in hospital. 
The couple were due to fly home that day. 
FACEBOOK PRETTY: Emily was just 20 years old 
Mr Keating reportedly told medics the young lovers crashed after being blinded by the sun glaring of the sea. 
But Thai police said they had arrested Mr Keating for causing death due to "carelessness" yesterday. 
EPA BATTLE: Thai lifeguards try to save Emily's life at Kata Beach “Fly high up there Emmy” Tommy Keating 
Mr Keating, 22, left a heart-breaking tribute to his girlfriend on Facebook. 
Posting pictures of the pair kissing and hugging, the apprentice plumber wrote: “My beautiful girl, taken from us far too soon. 
“I love you so much Emily and I wish I could just bring you back into my arms. 
“I’m so broken and I know I'll never, never be able to mend. 
FACEBOOK HAPPY COUPLE: Emily and Tommy had been together for two years 
“I’ll always be your boy and you'll always be my girl. We had so many plans for our future Emmy. 
“I love you to bits baby and I promise I'll never stop and you'll always have my heart. 
“You where such an inspiration to myself and many others. 
FACEBOOK PRINCESS: Everything 'shined bright' when Emily was around, her parents said 
“The most beautiful girl I’ve ever met – inside and out. 
“Fly high up there Emmy – I know you'll always be looking down on me and everyone you loved.” Top 20 travel destinations to visit in 2017 Wednesday, 4th January 2017 Where to be seen in 2017: Top 20 travel destinations for next year 1 / 20 Getty Images/AWL Images RM Dominican Republic 
The couple arrived in Thailand on January 26 and were scheduled to leave on Sunday, police said. 
They had been together for about two years and had gone to Thailand on a “dream holiday”, Mr Keating's cousin, Sean Lyon Smith said. 
Sanya Thongsawad, superintendent at Karon Provincial Police Station, said: "We are now collecting evidence and will have to initially press charges for carelessness, causing others to die."

Emily’s parents are due to fly in to collect her body tomorrow. 
In a statement, her family said: "Emily was our princess, everything shined bright when she was around. 
"She was the most caring person and deeply loved her family more than anything in the world. 
"She was looking forward to celebrating her 21st birthday this year and completing her pharmacy degree." Related articles
